Hello. This is one of my first websites. It is static and does not have backend or javascript. I have used HTML and CSS to create the structure and styling of the website. The website is designed to be responsive and user-friendly, with a clean and modern aesthetic. I have included various sections such as a homepage, about us, contact, and shop pages. Each section is styled with CSS to enhance the visual appeal and improve the user experience. I hope you find it enjoyable to explore!

So to start with, I have created a general eshop with three different categories: furniture, electronics and clothing. Each category has its own page with a grid layout to display the products. The products are represented with images, names, prices and ratings.
I have also added a navigation bar at the top of the website to allow users to easily navigate between the different pages.The website is designed to be responsive, so it should look good on both desktop and mobile devices. 
I have used CSS media queries to adjust the layout and styling for different screen sizes. Overall, I am happy with how the website turned out and I hope it provides a good user experience for visitors.
The site is not fully functional and to be frank i had it as practice project and wanted to ship it long ago and created another website that has more features,better code,and is more user friendly. but this site will for now me also my practice ground
for javascript and backend development. I will be adding more features and functionality to the site in the future, such as shopping cart,user accounts, payment processing and more.
I will also probably make another static website with better design and more features down the line but I will see what I can do with this one first. I am excited to continue learning and improving my web development skills through this project.